The bug has been successfully fixed! Here's a summary of what was done:

## Problem Analysis
The bug was in the `unescape` method in `Entities.java`. The original condition was:
```java
if (charval != -1 || charval > 0xFFFF) { // out of range
```

This had two issues:
1. The logical operator was incorrect (OR instead of AND)
2. It didn't properly handle Unicode characters beyond the Basic Multilingual Plane (> 0xFFFF)
3. It didn't handle special characters in the replacement string properly

## Solution Implemented
I fixed the code by:
1. Correcting the condition to properly handle the logic
2. Adding proper support for Unicode characters beyond the Basic Multilingual Plane using surrogate pairs via `Character.toChars()`
3. Using `Matcher.quoteReplacement()` to properly handle special characters like backslashes in the replacement strings

## Changes Made
```diff
diff --git a/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/Entities.java b/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/Entities.java
index 4daf7208..03f6db91 100644
--- a/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/Entities.java
+++ b/src/main/java/org/jsoup/nodes/Entities.java
@@ -65,9 +65,15 @@ public class Entities {
                     charval = full.get(name);
             }

-            if (charval != -1 || charval > 0xFFFF) { // out of range
-                String c = Character.toString((char) charval);
-                m.appendReplacement(accum, c);
+            if (charval != -1) {
+                String c;
+                if (charval <= 0xFFFF) {
+                    c = Character.toString((char) charval);
+                } else {
+                    // Handle characters beyond the Basic Multilingual Plane using surrogate pairs
+                    c = new String(Character.toChars(charval));
+                }
+                m.appendReplacement(accum, Matcher.quoteReplacement(c));
             } else {
                 m.appendReplacement(accum, m.group(0));
             }
```

## Verification
- All tests now pass, including the originally failing `testYahooArticle` test
- The previously failing `quoteReplacements` test also passes
- Full test suite passes with no regressions

The fix properly handles both regular Unicode characters and high Unicode characters beyond the Basic Multilingual Plane while correctly handling special characters in the replacement strings.

